Adaro Energy, Bumi Resources, Telkom: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-11T01:57:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/adaro-energy-bumi-resources-telkom-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 1.6 percent to 4,003.69.  Coal producers: Power-station coal  prices  at Australia’s
Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, increased 1.3 percent to
$122.45 in the week ended July 8, according to the  globalCOAL
NEWC Index . PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ),  Asia ’s largest exporter
of power-station coal, gained 1.7 percent to 3,025 rupiah and PT
Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ), the second largest, advanced 2 percent
to 2,600 rupiah.  Oil companies : Crude oil futures fell 2.5 percent to $96.20
a barrel in  New York  on July 8, the most in two weeks. Oil was
at $95.93 in after-hours trading today.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, was unchanged at 2,300 rupiah and PT
Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, climbed 0.5
percent to 200 rupiah.  PT Telekomunikasi  Indonesia  (TLKM IJ): The company’s first-
half revenue may rise 5 percent to 7 percent from a year earlier
to 33 trillion rupiah ($3.8 billion) to 34 trillion rupiah,
 Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing Finance Director Sudiro Asno.
Telkom, as the nation’s biggest telephone company is known, rose
0.7 percent to 7,200 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
